DURBAN - Three people were killed in a taxi crash in  Umzinyathi Drive, Inanda on Thursday afternoon. Kyle van Reenen of Crisis Medical, said the taxi veered off the road and down an embankment. "The taxi came to rest on its roof near one of the homesteads. Three people died at the scene while six more were seriously injured.  Ten other passengers sustained minor injuries. All the injured were stabilised at the scene before being rushed to hospital.  The cause of the collision is unknown," he said The deceased were ejected from the taxi while it was rolling. Police are investigating cases of culpable homicide. Earlier in the day, eight people were injured when a taxi rear-ended a bakkie  on the N2 north near Gateway. Daily News